<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="101" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="16.[136,1452,372,1913]" pageId="16" pageNumber="101">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,284,372,398]" pageId="16" pageNumber="101">Description:</emphasis>
—Stem and leaf scales present. Leaf bases connate. Lingulate leaves 0.6 × 5.0– 
<quantity box="[1235,1327,372,399]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="16" pageNumber="101" unit="mm" value="5.5">5.5 mm</quantity>
, expanded submerged or floating leaves broadly ovate, 2.3–4.9 × 
<quantity box="[765,904,408,434]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.35" metricValueMax="3.4" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="16" pageNumber="101" unit="mm" value="2.35" valueMax="3.4" valueMin="1.3">1.3–3.4 mm</quantity>
, petiole 1.6–4.7, 3-veined, occasionally with an additional loop on one of the secondary veins, apical leaves forming a floating rosette, leaves of terrestrial plants unknown. Bracts caducous, 0.6–1.0 mm. StYle erect, persistent, ≤ 
<quantity box="[874,963,478,505]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" pageId="16" pageNumber="101" unit="mm" value="2.6">2.6 mm</quantity>
. Filament erect, ≤ 
<quantity box="[1170,1259,478,505]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="16" pageNumber="101" unit="mm" value="5.5">5.5 mm</quantity>
; anther reniform, 
<quantity box="[136,273,513,540]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="101" unit="mm" value="0.45" valueMax="0.5" valueMin="0.4">0.4–0.5 mm</quantity>
diameter; pollen yellow. Fruit not strumose, subsessile, as high as or higher than wide, grey-brown to maroon when mature, 1.1–1.3 × 1.0– 
<quantity box="[552,639,549,575]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="16" pageNumber="101" unit="mm" value="1.2">1.2 mm</quantity>
, unwinged.
</paragraph>
